### ============================================================
### FOOD COMPETITION PLATFORM — API TEST FILE
### Use the REST Client VS Code extension (humao.rest-client)
### Click "Send Request" above each block to test
### ============================================================

### --- HEALTH CHECK ---
### Should return: { "status": "ok", "timestamp": "..." }
GET http://localhost:3001/health

### --- COMPETITIONS ---

### Get active competition
### Should return: Toronto Burger Battle 2025 with reward_config
GET http://localhost:3001/api/competitions/active

### --- RESTAURANTS ---

### Get all restaurants in active competition
### Should return: array of 5 restaurants with lat/lng coordinates
GET http://localhost:3001/api/restaurants

### Get single restaurant by ID (Apache Burger)
### Should return: full restaurant object with description, tags, photos
GET http://localhost:3001/api/restaurants/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111

### Get restaurant with invalid UUID
### Should return: 400 with "Invalid restaurant ID" message
GET http://localhost:3001/api/restaurants/not-a-valid-uuid

### Get restaurant that doesn't exist
### Should return: 404 with "Restaurant not found" message
GET http://localhost:3001/api/restaurants/99999999-9999-9999-9999-999999999999

### --- VISITS ---

### Record a visit (Test Explorer visits Apache Burger)
### Should return: 201 with the created visit object
POST http://localhost:3001/api/visits
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "aaaa1111-bbbb-cccc-dddd-eeee11111111",
  "restaurant_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "competition_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
  "geo_lat": 43.6502,
  "geo_lng": -79.3965
}

### Record DUPLICATE visit (same user, same restaurant)
### Should return: 409 with "Already visited" message
POST http://localhost:3001/api/visits
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "aaaa1111-bbbb-cccc-dddd-eeee11111111",
  "restaurant_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "competition_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
  "geo_lat": 43.6502,
  "geo_lng": -79.3965
}

### Visit with missing fields
### Should return: 400 with validation errors listing each missing field
POST http://localhost:3001/api/visits
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "aaaa1111-bbbb-cccc-dddd-eeee11111111"
}

### Visit with GPS at (0, 0) — broken GPS
### Should return: 400 with "GPS coordinates (0, 0) are invalid" message
POST http://localhost:3001/api/visits
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "aaaa1111-bbbb-cccc-dddd-eeee11111111",
  "restaurant_id": "22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222",
  "competition_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
  "geo_lat": 0,
  "geo_lng": 0
}

### Visit with non-existent restaurant
### Should return: 404 with "Restaurant not found" message
POST http://localhost:3001/api/visits
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "aaaa1111-bbbb-cccc-dddd-eeee11111111",
  "restaurant_id": "99999999-9999-9999-9999-999999999999",
  "competition_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
  "geo_lat": 43.6502,
  "geo_lng": -79.3965
}

